Rule Book

Rule 1: Worst Case
    We always search for the worst case into the function.

Rule 2: Remove Constants
    Ignore any constant numbers or multipliers.
    If an algorithm takes O(2n), O(500n), or O(n/2) time tom run, drop the constants and simply call it O(n).

Rule 3: Different terms for inputs
    Ex 1: Function(input1, input2)
    for (.. input : input1)...
    for (.. input : input2)...
    O(a + b)
    for (.. input : input1)...
        for (.. input : input2)...
    O(a * b)

    Ex 2: Function(input3)
    for (.. input : input3 ..)
    for (.. input : input3 ..)
    O(2n) = O(n)
    for (.. input : input3 ..)
        for (.. input : input3 ..)
    O(n * n) = O(n^2)

Rule 4: Drop non dominants
    n= 5
    n = 500
    O(n^2+3x+41+n/2)
    O(n^2)

